    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the sociological stuff but what about the actual deterrence factor? like if people know they're gonna face real consequences it's supposed to stop them from committing crimes in the first place. isnt there any data that shows strict sentencing actually prevents crime?",
