      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The data on deterrence is a clear and consistent debunking of the \"tough on crime\" narrative; studies from the 1970s onward have repeatedly shown that harsher penalties do not reduce crime rates, as the threat of execution or mandatory minimums fails to deter individuals who are already determined to commit crimes. Instead, the evidence overwhelmingly points to the fact that crime is driven by socioeconomic factors like poverty, lack of education, and mental health crises, which only punitive measures fail to address. The only proven solution is to invest in social programs, community support, and rehabilitation, because focusing solely on punishment only creates a cycle of incarceration without ever lowering crime.",
